ion: In partnership with the EEA Board, develop and communicate the organization's key priorities; guide the strategic vision of the EEA with the ability to lead and direct both short-term and long-term roadmaps; identify trends and industry issues that impact the organization and its work. Communicate the vision: promote and act as spokesperson for the EEA and its mission; proactively promote interest and participation; engage with audiences at industry conferences by speaking formally on behalf of the EEA; represent the EEA in the industry media by conducting interviews and providing comments to establish the EEA as an industry leader; work with EEA's Board of Directors to ensure the community and public affairs of the organization are consistently presented in a strong and positive image. Build the network: partner with the EEA leadership to identify new members; proactively solicit new members and sponsors; foster ongoing strategic relationships with members and the ecosystem at large. Forge and maintain strong collaborative ties with the Ethereum Foundation. Identify, build and maintain senior-level relationships with other industry and ecosystem decision makers. Steer execution: implement policies and activities authorized by the board of directors; support the development of position statements on policies and potential legislation that could impact the industry; negotiate and sign contracts on behalf of the association. Identify new developments in the Ethereum and decentralized protocols ecosystem and move to provide leadership to shepherd those developments towards maturity. Ensure delivery: own the key deliverables of the EEA (perception, adoption, and standards). Identify and address Ethereum perception issues; identify and address barriers to Ethereum adoption; identify and develop standards as needed to address the other goals via productive use of working groups, reference implementations, certification programs, and related tools. Develop and maintain high member satisfaction and engagement while ensuring financial sustainability of the organization. Qualifications This is a highly visible role including leading a consortium at the forefront of technology innovation and interacting with different groups of stakeholders. We are looking for a senior executive who has experience and can communicate well with both large enterprises and the startups ecosystem. Candidate should have technical experience and good understanding of blockchain technology as well as hands-on experience leading/participating in standards orgs. Qualifications Include, But Are Not Limited To Education: bachelor's degree required, master's degree preferred. PhD and/or MBA would be a strong plus. Experience: 15-20 years of progressive management experience, with extensive experience in enterprise IT management, ideally including IT infrastructure management and/or large IT project delivery, in partnership with large IT vendors as well as with small, specialized startups; proven track record of success in a leadership position overseeing operations of an organization or program, involving strategic planning, budgeting and client engagement, and developing solid relationships with top management and boards, staff, clients and community; experience in non-profit, standards-based organizations and/or participation in large scale open source projects would be considered a strong plus; startup experience as well as experience working within blockchain or related industry also a plus. Skills: technical competence with detailed knowledge and solid understanding of Ethereum and competing blockchain technologies; excellent communication and leadership skills and extensive experience in public speaking/public relations; self-management capabilities and entrepreneurial spirit; practical knowledge and ability to manage accounting, budgeting, finance and marketing; experience developing and implementing consortia and partnerships to achieve community-wide social and economic goals would be a strong plus. ", 
